"18:83:4" : {s: 18, a: 83, w: 4, r: "قرن", t: "ٱلْقَرْنَيْنِ", l: "قَرْن", lc: 23, tl: "l-qarnayni", lb: "যুগ",e: "Dhul-qarnain", b: "যুল কারনাইন", f: 3, rm: "to join one thing with another, couple. qarnin/qarnan - generation, century. qarn (dual qarnani, oblique qaraini, plu. qurun) - horn, trumpet. Often used to symbolise strength/power/glory. qarunun (pl. qurana) - mate, comrade, intimate companion. muqarranin - bound together. muqrinina - capable of subduing. muqtarinin - those formed in serried ranks, accompanying ones."},
"18:83:5" : {s: 18, a: 83, w: 5, r: "قول", t: "قُلْ", l: "قَالَ", lc: 1618, tl: "qul", lb: "কথা বলা",e: "Say", b: "তুমি বল", f: 218, rm: "to say/speak, to call, to be named, word/speech, utterance, a thing said, greeting, discourse, one who says/speaks. To inspire/transmit/relate/answer/think/profess, emit an opinion on, indicate a state or condition or circumstance. qailun - speaker, indicator."},
